<DOC><DOCNO> AP880702-0118 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-88 1512EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Turkey-Storms     07-02 0131</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Turkey-Storms,0134</SECOND><HEAD>Storm Kills Four, Five Missing</HEAD><DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three days of heavy rains in Turkeytriggered floods that killed three people and left five othersmissing, news agencies reported Saturday.   Two miners drowned Friday when flood waters poured into a coalmine in the Black Sea coastal province of Zonguldak, the AnatoliaNews Agency reported. An 85-year-old woman drowned in the easternprovince of Agri, the agency said.   In addition, a shepherd was reported dead after being struck bylightning in the eastern province of Erzurum.   Five people were missing in Ordu province in the Black Searegion after flood waters swept their jeep from a bridge, accordingto Anatolia.   The storms also flooded crops in the Ordu region, causing damageestimated at $200,000, the agency said.</TEXT></DOC>